<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="556" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,788,2039]" pageId="6" pageNumber="556">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,322,896,922]" pageId="6" pageNumber="556">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Female. The only Neotropical species of the 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Haliday" baseAuthorityYear="1833" box="[821,917,896,922]" class="Insecta" family="Ceratopogonidae" genus="Palpomyia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="556" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="distincta">
<emphasis box="[821,917,896,922]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="556">distincta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group with the following combination of characters: thorax dark brown, with a small paler humeral area near lateral margin; scutum with anterior tubercle; legs pale yellow; mid, hind coxae, femorotibial joints, and apex of hind femur dark brown; fore femur greatly swollen with 21–25 ventral spines, mid and hind femora without spines; tarsal claws small, subequal-size on all legs; abdomen paler; basal ½ of posterior portion of sternite 8 fused with distal section. Male unknown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,788,2039]" pageId="6" pageNumber="556">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,286,1076,1102]" pageId="6" pageNumber="556">Female</emphasis>
. Head (
<figureCitation box="[373,459,1076,1102]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1814,1838]" captionTargetBox="[162,1421,191,1774]" captionTargetId="figure-19@2.[151,1436,179,1788]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Heads, frontal view. A. Palpomyia aspina, female; B. P. subaspera, male; C. P. auakua sp. nov., female. Scale bars= 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5224035" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5224035/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="556">Fig. 1C</figureCitation>
). Dark brown, clypeus yellowish. Eyes separated by diameter of two ommatidia.Antennal flagellum (
<figureCitation box="[317,405,1112,1139]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[200,1388,191,1913]" captionTargetId="figure-31@7.[187,1401,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 5. Palpomyia auakua sp. nov., female. A. Flagellomeres, lateral view; B. Palpal segments 3–5; C. Femur and tibia of fore leg, lateral view; D. tarsal segment 5 of hind leg, lateral view. Scale bars: A= 0.64 mm; B, D= 0.04 mm; C= 0.16 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5224043" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5224043/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="556">Fig. 5A</figureCitation>
) with flagellomeres 9−13 and distal 1/3 of 1−12 dark brown, basal 2/3 pale yellow; flagel- lomeres 2–8 vasiform, 9–13 approximately 3x longer than 8; 13 longer than 12 with narrow, conical tip; antennal ratio (AR) 2.04−2.12 (2.08, n=2). Palpus (
<figureCitation box="[626,712,1184,1211]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[200,1388,191,1913]" captionTargetId="figure-31@7.[187,1401,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 5. Palpomyia auakua sp. nov., female. A. Flagellomeres, lateral view; B. Palpal segments 3–5; C. Femur and tibia of fore leg, lateral view; D. tarsal segment 5 of hind leg, lateral view. Scale bars: A= 0.64 mm; B, D= 0.04 mm; C= 0.16 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5224043" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5224043/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="556">Fig. 5B</figureCitation>
) brown; segment 3 slender, elongate with 4–5 capitate sensillae; palpal ratio (
<collectingRegion box="[291,328,1220,1246]" country="Brazil" name="Para" pageId="6" pageNumber="556">PR</collectingRegion>
) 4.0 (n=2). Mandible with 7 large teeth. Thorax (
<figureCitation box="[873,960,1220,1246]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1214,1238]" captionTargetBox="[160,1426,191,1186]" captionTargetId="figure-31@3.[151,1436,181,1190]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Thorax, lateral view. Females. A. Palpomyia aspina; B. P. auakua sp. nov. Scale bars= 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5224037" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5224037/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="556">Fig. 2B</figureCitation>
). Dark brown, except a small pale humeral area near lateral margin. Scutum with anterior tubercle; sparsely covered with short setae, 3 supra-alar setae, one posterior seta near scutellum; scutellum with 4 large setae. Legs (
<figureCitation box="[875,950,1292,1318]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[220,1364,189,1911]" captionTargetId="figure-19@4.[216,1372,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 3. Legs, lateral view.A−C. Palpomyia subaspera, male; D−F. P. auakua sp. nov., female. A, D= fore legs; B, E= mid legs; C, F= hind legs. Scale bars= 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5224039" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5224039/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="556">Figs. 3</figureCitation>
D−F, 5C−D) pale yellow; mid, -hind coxae, femorotibial joints, apex of hind femur and tarsomeres 4–5 dark brown; fore femur greatly swollen with 21–25 ventral spines (
<figureCitation box="[282,370,1364,1391]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[200,1388,191,1913]" captionTargetId="figure-31@7.[187,1401,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 5. Palpomyia auakua sp. nov., female. A. Flagellomeres, lateral view; B. Palpal segments 3–5; C. Femur and tibia of fore leg, lateral view; D. tarsal segment 5 of hind leg, lateral view. Scale bars: A= 0.64 mm; B, D= 0.04 mm; C= 0.16 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5224043" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5224043/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="556">Fig. 5C</figureCitation>
), mid, -hind femora without spines; tarsomeres 1–2 of hind leg with 2 rows of ventral palisade setae; tarsomere 5 of hind leg (
<figureCitation box="[498,586,1400,1427]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[200,1388,191,1913]" captionTargetId="figure-31@7.[187,1401,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 5. Palpomyia auakua sp. nov., female. A. Flagellomeres, lateral view; B. Palpal segments 3–5; C. Femur and tibia of fore leg, lateral view; D. tarsal segment 5 of hind leg, lateral view. Scale bars: A= 0.64 mm; B, D= 0.04 mm; C= 0.16 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5224043" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5224043/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="556">Fig. 5D</figureCitation>
) with 2−3 slender, straight, ventrolateral setae with pointed tips; claws sub- equal-size (
<figureCitation box="[279,342,1436,1462]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[220,1364,189,1911]" captionTargetId="figure-19@4.[216,1372,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 3. Legs, lateral view.A−C. Palpomyia subaspera, male; D−F. P. auakua sp. nov., female. A, D= fore legs; B, E= mid legs; C, F= hind legs. Scale bars= 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5224039" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5224039/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="556">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
D−F), hind claws longest. Wing (
<figureCitation box="[713,798,1436,1462]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1376,1400]" captionTargetBox="[157,1423,194,1342]" captionTargetId="figure-31@5.[151,1436,181,1352]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 4. Wings, frontal view. A. Palpomyia aspina, female; B. P. subaspera, male; C. P. auakua sp. nov., female. Scale bars= 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5224041" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5224041/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="556">Fig. 4C</figureCitation>
) membrane pale; all veins pale brown; M broadly sessile, distance between r-m crossvein and base of M 
<subScript attach="left" box="[674,682,1490,1504]" fontSize="6" pageId="6" pageNumber="556">2</subScript>
slightly shorter than r-m; 2nd radial cell 2.7x longer than 1 
<superScript attach="none" box="[1354,1365,1472,1486]" fontSize="6" pageId="6" pageNumber="556">st</superScript>
; wing length 
<quantity box="[228,392,1508,1535]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.55" metricValueMax="2.6" metricValueMin="2.5" pageId="6" pageNumber="556" unit="mm" value="2.55" valueMax="2.6" valueMin="2.5">2.50−2.60 mm</quantity>
(
<quantity box="[406,510,1508,1535]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.55" pageId="6" pageNumber="556" unit="mm" value="2.55">2.55 mm</quantity>
; n=2), width 0.74−0.82 (
<quantity box="[785,889,1508,1535]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.8" pageId="6" pageNumber="556" unit="mm" value="0.78">0.78 mm</quantity>
; n=2); costal ratio (CR) 0.79 (n=2). Halter white. Abdomen. (
<figureCitation box="[284,360,1544,1571]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[286,1311,198,1907]" captionTargetId="figure-19@8.[264,1324,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 6. Female abdomens (A, C−D) and male genitalia (B). A. Palpomyia aspina, dorsal view; B. P. subaspera, male genitalia, ventral view; C−D. P. auakua sp. nov., ventral view. Scale bars: A, C= 0.5 mm; B, D= 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5224045" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5224045/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="556">Figs. 6</figureCitation>
C−D) pale yellow. Sternite 8 anterior portion lightly sclerotized, with 1−2 lateral setae and ca.14 large, mesal setae, its margin hyaline, posterior margin convex; posterior portion slightly sclerotized, fused on basal 1/2, distal ½ divided, each plate elongate, gradually tapering posteriorly with pointed sclerotized tips; and 2 lateral, setose lobes that extend ¾ of plates length. Sternite 9 lightly sclerotized with a pair of slender anteriorly directed arms. Sternite 10 V-shaped with 3–5 pairs of large setae. Two globular, subequal-size spermathecae (
<figureCitation box="[1283,1370,1688,1715]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[286,1311,198,1907]" captionTargetId="figure-19@8.[264,1324,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 6. Female abdomens (A, C−D) and male genitalia (B). A. Palpomyia aspina, dorsal view; B. P. subaspera, male genitalia, ventral view; C−D. P. auakua sp. nov., ventral view. Scale bars: A, C= 0.5 mm; B, D= 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5224045" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5224045/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="556">Fig. 6D</figureCitation>
) with narrow, short necks, measuring 0.070 by 
<quantity box="[612,728,1724,1751]" metricMagnitude="-5" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.0" pageId="6" pageNumber="556" unit="mm" value="0.05">0.050 mm</quantity>
, and 0.065 by 
<quantity box="[892,995,1724,1751]" metricMagnitude="-5" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.0" pageId="6" pageNumber="556" unit="mm" value="0.04">0.04 mm</quantity>
; plus, a rudimentary 3rd spermatheca.
</paragraph>
