<collectingRegion box="[459,549,1796,1822]" country="Mexico" name="Hidalgo" pageId="6" pageNumber="556">Hidalgo</collectingRegion>
(Tlanchinol) (
<figureCitation box="[711,780,1796,1823]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="9.[151,250,1488,1512]" captionTargetBox="[155,1433,568,1461]" captionTargetId="figure-231@9.[151,1436,561,1465]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURE 7. Distributions in Mexico. Palpomyia aspina, black rectangle; P. subaspera, black circle; P. auakua sp. nov., black triangle." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5224047" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5224047/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="556">Fig. 7</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="556" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,788,2039]" pageId="6" pageNumber="556">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,328,1832,1858]" pageId="6" pageNumber="556">Etymology</emphasis>
. The specific name is an abbreviation of the word “ 
<emphasis box="[928,1068,1832,1858]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="556">auakuautlan</emphasis>
” = forest cloud, in Nahualt lan- guage.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="9" lastPageNumber="559" pageId="6" pageNumber="556" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,788,2039]" pageId="6" pageNumber="556">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,325,1904,1930]" pageId="6" pageNumber="556">Discussion</emphasis>
. This new species is typical of other spp. in the 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Haliday" baseAuthorityYear="1833" box="[889,985,1904,1930]" class="Insecta" family="Ceratopogonidae" genus="Palpomyia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="556" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="distincta">
<emphasis box="[889,985,1904,1930]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="556">distincta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group by their pale yellowish legs and greatly swollen fore femur with 21–25 black, ventral spines. 
<taxonomicName authority="Spinelli et al. 2009" authorityName="Spinelli" authorityYear="2009" box="[828,1262,1940,1967]" class="Insecta" family="Ceratopogonidae" genus="Palpomyia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="556" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="yamana">
<emphasis box="[828,1044,1940,1966]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="556">Palpomyia yamana</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Spinelli, G. R. &amp; Grogan, W. L. Jr. &amp; Ronderos, M. M." box="[1050,1262,1940,1967]" pageId="6" pageNumber="556" pagination="43 - 70" refId="ref5925" refString="Spinelli, G. R., Grogan, W. L. Jr. &amp; Ronderos, M. M. (2009) A revision of the Patagonian predaceous midges of the genus Palpomyia Meigen (Diptera: Ceratopogonidae). Insect Systematics &amp; Evolution, 40, 43 - 70. https: // doi. org / 10.1163 / 187631209 X 416705" type="journal article" year="2009">
Spinelli 
<emphasis box="[1144,1192,1940,1966]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="556">et al</emphasis>
. 2009
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingRegion country="Argentina" name="Tierra del Fuego - Antartida e Islas del Atlantico Sur" pageId="6" pageNumber="556">Tierra del Fuego</collectingRegion>
, has similar legs but the abdomen has 4 pairs of gland rods, hind tarsomere 5 has 4-5 pairs of stouter ventral setae with recurved tips and the hind claws are distinctly longer than those of fore and -midlegs.
</paragraph>
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5224043" ID-Zenodo-Dep="5224043" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5224043/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="557" startId="7.[151,250,1943,1967]" targetBox="[200,1388,191,1913]" targetPageId="7">
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1436,1943,2004]" pageId="7" pageNumber="557">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,275,1943,1968]" pageId="7" pageNumber="557">FIGURE 5.</emphasis>
