<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1437,151,537]" pageId="9" pageNumber="559">
It is also similar to other two Neotropical species from 
<collectingCountry box="[815,886,151,177]" name="Brazil" pageId="9" pageNumber="559">Brazil</collectingCountry>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Lane, 1947" authorityName="Lane" authorityYear="1947" box="[897,1189,151,177]" class="Insecta" family="Ceratopogonidae" genus="Palpomyia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="559" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="paulistensis">
<emphasis box="[897,1056,151,177]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="559">P. paulistensis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Lane, J." box="[1064,1189,151,177]" pageId="9" pageNumber="559" pagination="438 - 447" refId="ref5646" refString="Lane, J. (1947) Novas especies de Palpomyia do Brasil (Diptera, Ceratopogonidae). Revista de Entomologia, 18 (3), 438 - 447." type="journal article" year="1947">Lane, 1947</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Macfie, 1939" authorityName="Macfie" authorityYear="1939" class="Insecta" family="Ceratopogonidae" genus="Palpomyia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="559" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="castanea">
<emphasis box="[1243,1371,151,176]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="559">P. castanea</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Macfie, J. W. S." pageId="9" pageNumber="559" pagination="137 - 219" refId="ref5678" refString="Macfie, J. W. S. (1939) A report on a collection of Brazilian Ceratopogonidae (Dipt.). Revista de Entomologia, 10 (1), 137 - 219." type="journal article" year="1939">Macfie, 1939</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
which have similar leg coloration. However, in both of these species the halter knob is dark brown. Also, in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lane" authorityYear="1947" box="[151,314,223,249]" class="Insecta" family="Ceratopogonidae" genus="Palpomyia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="559" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="paulistensis">
<emphasis box="[151,168,223,248]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="559">P</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[182,314,223,249]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="559">paulistensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
the scutum, scutellum and postscutellum are shining black, the apex of the fore femur is dark brown and abdominal sternite 4 has a distinct dark spot. And in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Macfie" authorityYear="1939" box="[790,921,259,285]" class="Insecta" family="Ceratopogonidae" genus="Palpomyia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="559" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="castanea">
<emphasis box="[790,807,259,284]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="559">P</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[821,921,259,284]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="559">castanea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
the scutum is dark brown with extensive pale yellowish-brown areas, the scutellum is also yellowish-brown, the fore femur has only 8-9 stout black spines, and the abdomen is shining dark brown and has four pairs of gland rods.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1437,151,537]" pageId="9" pageNumber="559">
In the key by 
<bibRefCitation author="Grogan, W. L. Jr. &amp; Wirth, W. W." box="[352,617,367,393]" pageId="9" pageNumber="559" pagination="1 - 125" refId="ref5432" refString="Grogan, W. L. Jr. &amp; Wirth, W. W. (1979) The North American predaceous midges of the genus Palpomyia Meigen (Diptera: Ceratopogonidae). Memoirs of the Entomological Society of Washington, 8, i - vi, + 1 - 125." type="journal article" year="1979">Grogan &amp; Wirth (1979)</bibRefCitation>
of Nearctic species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Meigen" authorityYear="1818" box="[874,995,367,393]" class="Insecta" family="Ceratopogonidae" genus="Palpomyia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="559" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[874,995,367,393]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="559">Palpomyia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Huerta &amp; Spinelli, 2021" authorityName="Huerta &amp; Spinelli" authorityYear="2021" box="[1009,1122,367,393]" class="Insecta" family="Ceratopogonidae" genus="Palpomyia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="559" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="auakua" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[1009,1026,367,392]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="559">P</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[1040,1122,367,393]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="559">auakua</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1129,1218,367,393]" pageId="9" pageNumber="559">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1129,1218,367,393]" pageId="9" pageNumber="559" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
keys to couplet 19, 
<taxonomicName authority="Grogan &amp; Wirth, 1979" authorityName="Grogan &amp; Wirth. Also" authorityYear="1979" box="[151,559,403,429]" class="Insecta" family="Ceratopogonidae" genus="Palpomyia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="559" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="jamnbacki">
<emphasis box="[151,296,403,429]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="559">P. jamnbacki</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Grogan, W. L. Jr. &amp; Wirth, W. W." box="[302,559,403,429]" pageId="9" pageNumber="559" pagination="1 - 125" refId="ref5432" refString="Grogan, W. L. Jr. &amp; Wirth, W. W. (1979) The North American predaceous midges of the genus Palpomyia Meigen (Diptera: Ceratopogonidae). Memoirs of the Entomological Society of Washington, 8, i - vi, + 1 - 125." type="journal article" year="1979">Grogan &amp; Wirth, 1979</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. However, in the latter species the palpus, scutellum and abdomen are yellowish, the flagellomeres 9–13 are shorter (antennal ratio 1.57), the fore femur is moderately swollen with only 15-17 ventral spines, the hind femur has 3 ventral spines, the abdomen has one pair of gland rods and the posterior sections of sternite 8 are completely separated.
</paragraph>
